The paper deals with lower bounds for space complexity of graph processing algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The lower bounds are obtained through communication complexity lower bounds, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph theoretic arguments, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves information theory arguments, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
